HEADWORD: Tubiporite
<hw>Tu"bi*po*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>Any fossil coral of the genus <gen>Syringopora</gen> consisting of
a cluster of upright tubes united together by small transverse
tubules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tubivalve</ent>⟦br⟧
